{"id":840600432,"question_id":42,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 7 months","timestamp":1668064973,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/840600432/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Trapping Rain Water","memory":"49.2 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int trap(int[] height) {\n        int l=0, r=height.length-1;\n        int maxL=height[l], maxR = height[r];\n        \n        \n        int res=0;\n        while(l<r){\n            \n            if(maxL<=maxR){\n                \n                l++;\n                maxL = Math.max(maxL, height[l]);\n                res += maxL-height[l];\n                \n            }else{\n                r--;\n                maxR = Math.max(maxR, height[r]);\n                res+= maxR- height[r];\n            }\n        }\n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"trapping-rain-water","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
